@startuml 24-receipt-mixing-detail
title UReceipt Mixing Detail — R_{t+1} = mix(R_t, I, ΔU)

skinparam shadowing false

participant "UDelta Builder\n(Plane S)" as DB
participant "UReceipt Mixer" as RM
participant "Receipt State\n(rolling hash R_t)" as RS
participant "DeltaTape" as DT

DB -> RM : instruction_id: u64\nscope: u64\nfired_mask: u64\nUDelta { changed_words[] }

RM -> RS : read R_t (current receipt hash)

RM -> RM : material = [\n  R_t.to_le_bytes(),\n  instruction_id.to_le_bytes(),\n  scope.to_le_bytes(),\n  fired_mask.to_le_bytes(),\n  ΔU bytes (sparse changed words)\n]

RM -> RM : R_{t+1} = fnv1a_64(material)\n(deterministic — same inputs → same receipt)

note right of RM
  FNV-1a chosen: no-alloc, inline,
  constant-time per-word, no key-scheduling.
  Receipts are proof-of-motion, not
  cryptographic commitments.
  Independent replay must produce
  identical R_{t+1} from same inputs.
end note

RM -> RS : write R_{t+1}

RM -> DT : attach fragment {\n  epoch, instruction_id,\n  fired_mask, R_{t+1}\n} to tape entry

DT --> RM : tape position confirmed

note right of DT
  DeltaTape stores the minimal evidence
  needed to replay and verify any epoch.
  Projections (UProjection) are derived
  from ΔU + tape — not authoritative.
end note

@enduml
